{"body_text": "Fixes #1051\n\nCorrects bug where passing in inherited props broke the displayed placeholder.\n\nSpecifies which props to inherit, adds them to propTypes and defaultProps as appropriate\n\n\nAdds tests to determine that ExtensionSelect works and that the placeholder appears.\nAdds a tests/mockStore.js util file that allows us to wrap a component in a Provider with a mock store. This was needed in order to mount the component, since there is a nested Query component which is connected and requires a store etc.", "labels": [], "number": 1053, "assignee": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rehandalal/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rehandalal/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rehandalal/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rehandalal", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rehandalal/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/rehandalal", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rehandalal/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/987136?v=4", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rehandalal/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rehandalal/received_events", "gravatar_id": "", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rehandalal/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "site_admin": false, "login": "rehandalal", "type": "User", "id": 987136, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rehandalal/followers"}, "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy", "closed_at": "2017-09-11T18:18:09Z", "body_html": "<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #1051.\">Fixes</span> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"256295480\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/issues/1051\" href=\"https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/issues/1051\">#1051</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Corrects bug where passing in inherited props broke the displayed placeholder.\n<ul>\n<li>Specifies which props to inherit, adds them to <code>propTypes</code> and <code>defaultProps</code> as appropriate</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Adds tests to determine that <code>ExtensionSelect</code> works and that the placeholder appears.</li>\n<li>Adds a <code>tests/mockStore.js</code> util file that allows us to wrap a component in a <code>Provider</code> with a mock <code>store</code>. This was needed in order to <code>mount</code> the component, since there is a nested Query component which is <code>connect</code>ed and requires a store etc.</li>\n</ul>", "id": 256313497, "title": "#1051: Fix ExtensionSelect placeholder", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/pulls/1053", "diff_url": "https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/1053.diff", "html_url": "https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/1053", "patch_url": "https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/1053.patch"}, "comments": 4, "state": "closed", "body": "Fixes #1051 \r\n\r\n- Corrects bug where passing in inherited props broke the displayed placeholder.\r\n  - Specifies which props to inherit, adds them to `propTypes` and `defaultProps` as appropriate\r\n- Adds tests to determine that `ExtensionSelect` works and that the placeholder appears.\r\n- Adds a `tests/mockStore.js` util file that allows us to wrap a component in a `Provider` with a mock `store`. This was needed in order to `mount` the component, since there is a nested Query component which is `connect`ed and requires a store etc.", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/issues/1053/events", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/issues/1053/labels{/name}", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/normandy/issues/1053/comments", "html_url": "https://github.com/mozilla/normandy/pull/1053", "updated